@jorgebastida - I don't think you quite understand - this PR does not implement MFA, it simply adds support for reading and writing to the AWS CLI generated session cache.  

Also the AWS CLI natively supports MFA so you don't need another utility for this (i.e. https://github.com/jorgebastida/aws2fa) - see http://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/cli-roles.html#cli-roles-mfa

If you try and use `awslogs` currently with an MFA enabled CLI profile you will be prompted for MFA token (this is part of the boto3 library).  If you run `awslogs` again you will be prompted for MFA again ...and again... and again - without support for the session cache, you will always have this problem.

