Hi @aoman89757 ,

If I may, I may be able to provide at least a clue as to the cause? I've seen this before, and I believe (I could be wrong?) it has to do with the quality of the predictions as allowed by your configuration. If predictions (predicted cells) aren't being predicted the classifier's votes are spread across all the buckets evenly (as it is during the first several cycles). In particular I would pay attention to these 3 parameters, and the number of Cells and Columns:  

```Java
        parameters.setParameterByKey(KEY.SYN_PERM_INACTIVE_DEC, 0.01);
        parameters.setParameterByKey(KEY.SYN_PERM_ACTIVE_INC, 0.1);

        // There are rules for this one based on a percentage of sync_perm_active_inc I believe
        parameters.setParameterByKey(KEY.SYN_PERM_TRIM_THRESHOLD, 0.005); 
```
Those are the Java version's parameters but the names are easy to translate to the Python version...

try that... I may be wrong, but I think that might help? At least until Marion or Marcus are able to reply...

